DynaMed Level 2 (mid-level) evidence suggests the following [1]
Higher SIPAT scores not associated with increased mortality or organ failure
Higher SIPAT scores are associated with increased posttransplant rejection, hospitalization, infection, psychiatric complications, and support system failure in adults 1 year after organ transplant
SIPAT scorepredicted probabilities for any adverse outcome (medical + psychosocial) [3].\u2028()
